Median of (cash from operations \u00f7 net profit) over the last 5 years.","why_useful":"Profit you can't collect as cash is fragile; >0.8\u00d7 means earnings are real cash, <0.6\u00d7 is an accrual red flag.","why_it_can_fail":"One-off working-capital swings or a capex year can distort a single ratio; the 5-yr median smooths it."},{"label":"Balance-sheet safety","value":0.69,"unit":"\u00d7 D/E","status":"ok","read":"Moderate leverage (D/E 0.69\u00d7, interest cover 3.4\u00d7).","meaning":"Latest debt-to-equity and interest coverage (EBIT \u00f7 interest) from the balance sheet.","why_useful":"Low debt and high interest cover let a business survive a downturn; high debt amplifies trouble.","why_it_can_fail":"Off-balance-sheet leases/guarantees aren't captured; a cash-rich firm can show low D/E yet still be risky elsewhere."},{"label":"Earnings momentum","value":13.33,"unit":"% YoY","status":"ok","read":"Profit up 13% YoY \u2014 modest.","meaning":"Trailing-twelve-month net profit vs the year-ago TTM (and whether the YoY rate is rising = 'accelerating').","why_useful":"Improving, accelerating earnings tend to drive re-rating; falling profit warns of a deteriorating business.","why_it_can_fail":"TTM can be lumpy for cyclicals/one-offs; cross-check the multi-year trend on the Fundamentals tab."}]},"valuation":{"ok":true,"is_bank":false,"pe_now":76.7,"pe_percentile":69.0,"median_pe":70.7,"earnings_yield_pct":1.3,"pb":10.24,"ev_ebitda":33.55,"quality_score":49.0,"pat_cagr_5y_pct":136.1,"peg":0.56,"cheapness":{"status":"ok","read":"P/E at the 69-percentile of its 10-yr range \u2014 mid-range vs its own history."},"expectations":"At 76.7\u00d7 earnings for ~136% 5-yr profit CAGR, the market is paying \u22480.56\u00d7 growth (PEG). >2 = a lot already priced in; <1 = cheap if growth holds. This PEG divides TTM P/E by TRAILING 5-year annual PAT CAGR (endpoint-to-endpoint) \u2014 a time-axis mismatch vs the textbook FORWARD-EPS PEG, and one abnormal base/terminal year distorts the CAGR. A rough trailing valuation-vs-growth gauge, not a precise forward PEG.","cyclical_caveat":null,"meaning":"P/E percentile = where today's price-to-earnings sits within the stock's own last-10-yr range (low = cheap vs its past). Paired with the Quality score and 5-yr profit growth so a cheap multiple is judged against business strength, not in isolation.","why_useful":"Cheapness only matters relative to quality and growth \u2014 a low P/E on a declining or peak-cyclical business is a trap, not a bargain.","why_it_can_fail":"P/E breaks for loss-makers / one-offs; for banks use P/B not EV/EBITDA; a multiple cheap vs history can stay cheap if the business has structurally de-rated."},"ownership":{"ok":true,"na":null,"holders":{"Promoter":{"periods":["Jun 2024","Sep 2024","Dec 2024","Mar 2025","Jun 2025","Sep 2025","Dec 2025","Mar 2026"],"values":[80.91,80.91,80.91,80.91,80.91,80.91,80.91,80.91],"latest_pct":80.91,"chg_1y_pp":0.0},"FII":{"periods":["Jun 2024","Sep 2024","Dec 2024","Mar 2025","Jun 2025","Sep 2025","Dec 2025","Mar 2026"],"values":[3.83,2.83,2.55,2.73,2.82,2.96,3.36,3.23],"latest_pct":3.23,"chg_1y_pp":0.5},"DII":{"periods":["Jun 2024","Sep 2024","Dec 2024","Mar 2025","Jun 2025","Sep 2025","Dec 2025","Mar 2026"],"values":[3.52,4.14,4.01,4.03,4.73,4.56,4.61,4.82],"latest_pct":4.82,"chg_1y_pp":0.79},"Public":{"periods":["Jun 2024","Sep 2024","Dec 2024","Mar 2025","Jun 2025","Sep 2025","Dec 2025","Mar 2026"],"values":[11.73,12.11,12.53,12.33,11.53,11.58,11.12,11.03],"latest_pct":11.03,"chg_1y_pp":-1.3}},"pledge":null,"events":[{"date":"27-Jun-2025","subject":"Dividend - Rs 3.60 Per Share","materiality":"Low"},{"date":"25-Jun-2026","subject":"Dividend - Rs 5.40 Per Share","materiality":"Low"}],"placeholders":[{"label":"Promoter pledge (detail)","note":"share-level pledge history \u2014 fetchable via NSE, deferred to MVP-2."},{"label":"Bulk / block deals","note":"large on-market trades \u2014 NSE feed, deferred to MVP-2."},{"label":"Insider / SAST disc